    <text>
        <body>
            <head>28. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rec5nWAotd8wedNxI">Clark</persName>) to President <persName
                    corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName><note n="1" place="foot"
                    type="source" xml:id="d28fn1">Source: National Security Council, <orgName
                        corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>
                    Institutional Files, Box SR 078, <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> 0044
                        [<gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event"
                            >START</rs></gloss> Negotiations III]. Secret. Sent for action. Prepared
                    by <persName corresp="rec3WaAgwEDeqcFLV">Linhard</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="rec1MI7pNjlwnDZyR">Kramer</persName>. A stamped notation at the top
                    of the memorandum reads: “signed.”</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1982-07-08"
                        >July 8, 1982</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> Reflecting Decisions Made At June
                    25 <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"><orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma"
                        >NSC</orgName></gloss> Luncheon</item>
            </list>
            <p>
                <hi rendition="simple_italic">Issue:</hi> Should you sign and document your
                decisions reached at the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"><orgName
                        corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">NSC</orgName></gloss> luncheon on <gloss
                    target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event"
                    >START</rs></gloss> on June 25?<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d28fn2">No
                    minutes were found. See <ref target="#d26">Document 26</ref>.</note>
            </p>
            <p>
                <hi rendition="simple_italic">Discussion:</hi> The attached draft National Security
                Decision Directive reflects the decision that you announced at the <gloss
                    target="#t_NSC_1"><orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">NSC</orgName></gloss>
                luncheon on <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event"
                        >START</rs></gloss> held on June 25. This would be the third <gloss
                    target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> on this subject. It continues the chain of
                documentation on decisions reached concerning the U.S. approach to the <gloss
                    target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event"
                    >START</rs></gloss> negotiations.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation:</p>
            <table cols="3">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>That you sign the draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>.<note n="3"
                            place="foot" xml:id="d28fn3"><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq"
                                >Reagan</persName> did not indicate his preference. The decision
                            directed is printed below as <ref target="#d29">Document
                            29</ref>.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
